<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<title>Welcome to DADI Web</title>
	</head>

	<style type="text/css">
		body {
			margin: 0;
			font-family: Courier, "Lucida Sans Typewriter", "Lucida Typewriter", monospace;
			-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
			-moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
		}
		.version {
			background: #e42918;
			color: #fff;
			padding: 2px 5px;
			display: inline-block;
		}
		h1,h2 {
			font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
		}
		.file {
			background: #f5f5f5;
			padding: 0 4px;
		}
		header {
			background: #f5f5f5;
		}
		code {
			background: #f5f5f5;
			display: block;
			padding: 1px 20px;
			margin: 20px 0;
			line-height: 1.4em;
		}
		a, h1 {
			color: #e42918;
		}
		ol {
			margin: 0;
			padding: 0;
		}
		li {
			margin: 30px 0;
			counter-increment: step-counter;
			position: relative;
			list-style: none;
			line-height: 1.4em;
		}
		li:before {
			content: counter(step-counter);
			background-color: #fff;
			border: 1px solid #E8E8E8;
			color: #000;
			font-weight: bold;
			line-height: 35px;
			vertical-align: middle;
			width: 35px; height: 35px;
			text-align: center;
			border-radius: 40px;
			position: absolute;
			top: -5px; left: -60px;
		}

		header, .page {
			padding: 40px 0 40px 200px;
		}

		.page {
			max-width: 600px;
			border-left: 1px solid #E8E8E8;
		}
		.logo {
			position: fixed;
			top: 0; left: 0; bottom: 0;
			padding: 50px 40px;
			border-right: 1px solid #E8E8E8;
		}
		.logo img {
			display: block;
			width: 80px;
		}
	</style>
<body>

<div class="logo">
	<img src="dadi-web.png">
</div>

<header>
	<p class="version">DADI Web {version}</p>

	<h1>Successfully installed and running!</h1>
	<p>Explore the <a href="http://docs.dadi.tech">documentation</a> and the source code to our site as an <a href="https://github.com/dadi/dadi.tech">example project</a>.</p>
</header>

<div class="page">

	<h2>Things to try</h2>

	<ol>
		<li>You are looking at <span class="file">workspace/pages/index.dust</span>. Try changing something in this file to see it updated here. </li>
		<li>Create your first datasource. Here is an example of a markdown based one:

		<code><pre>
			{<br>
			&nbsp; "datasource": {<br>
			&nbsp;   "key": "articles",<br>
			&nbsp;   "name": "Latest blog posts.",<br>
			&nbsp;   "source": {<br>
			&nbsp;     "type": "markdown",<br>
			&nbsp;     "path": "../posts"<br>
			&nbsp;   },<br>
			&nbsp;   "paginate": true,<br>
			&nbsp;   "count": 10,<br>
			&nbsp;   "sort": {<br>
			&nbsp;     "date": -1<br>
			&nbsp;   },<br>
			&nbsp;   "requestParams": [<br>
			&nbsp;     {<br>
			&nbsp;       "param": "article", "field": "handle"<br>
			&nbsp;     }<br>
			&nbsp;   ]<br>
			&nbsp; }<br>
			}
		</pre></code>
		</li>

		<li>Learn more about <a href="https://dadi.tech/platform/api/">DADI API</a> and how you can use it with your new installation of DADI Web</li>
	</ol>
</div>

</body>
</html>